name: Cell Biology
description: This course is designed to introduce theory and modern experimental techniques in cell biology. Emphasis will be on eukaryotic cells. Structure and function of major animal and plant organelles will be covered. Subsequent topics include the role of the cytoskeleton. Plasma membrane and extracellular matrix will also be detailed in the context of cell interactions with the environment.
prerequisites: BIOA01H3 and BIOA02H3 and CHMA10H3 and CHMA11H3
